comment:
I don't think that Mr. Depp is "innocent", but like hell is Amber Heard "innocent" either! My issue is not that Mr. Depp lost the case, it's that, without any evidence and based on evidence to the contrary, the courts SIDED with Amber Heard and simply believed her anyway. Could Mr. Depp have lost, absolutely. But, once upon a time, "He said, She said" cases used to be thrown out because of insufficient evidence and the courts didn't take a side. Now the courts take a side based on "feelings" not law, and not facts. That is the very definition of abuse of power and it's disgusting! To throw your power and authority behind something that can not be substantiated by fact is setting a legal precedent of abuse of power!

I will say it over and over again, setting a legal precedent of abuse is STILL WRONG! It is evil in the extreme to establish a legal basis for judging with malice that for which you have ZERO proof! A legal precedent of abuse (in this case, of power) is STILL abuse!
